==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Senecas
<hw>Sen"e*cas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Seneca</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A
tribe of Indians who formerly inhabited a part of Western New York. This
tribe was the most numerous and most warlike of the Five
Nations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Seneca grass</b></col><fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>holy grass.
See under <er>Holy</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Seneca eil</b></col>,
<cd>petroleum or naphtha.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Seneca root</b></col>,
<it>or</it> <col><b>Seneca snakeroot</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>the rootstock of an American species of milkworth (<spn>Polygala
Senega</spn>) having an aromatic but bitter taste. It is often used
medicinally as an expectorant and diuretic, and, in large doses, as an
emetic and cathartic.</cd> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Senega root</asp>,
and <asp>Seneka root</asp>.]</altsp></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Senecio</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
